COMMENDATIONS. Commends Cheniere Energy on twenty years of investment,
leadership, and innovation, and ten years of LNG export operations in the state.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Cheniere Energy for over twenty years of investment, economic leadership,
3 and energy innovation, as well as ten years of LNG export operations in the state of
4 Louisiana, and to recognize the company's contributions to job creation, economic
5 growth, and the global energy marketplace.
6 WHEREAS, Cheniere Energy has become a global leader in the production and
7 export of liquefied natural gas (LNG), helping to strengthen the energy sector of the state
8 of Louisiana and the United States; and
9 WHEREAS, the company's major operations in Cameron Parish, including the
10 Sabine Pass Liquefaction Terminal, have positioned Louisiana as a premier hub for LNG
11 exports and a vital link in global energy supply chains; and
12 WHEREAS, Cheniere Energy has invested billions of dollars into Louisiana's
13 infrastructure and workforce, supporting thousands of construction and permanent jobs and
14 fostering economic development throughout southwest Louisiana and beyond; and
15 WHEREAS, the company's presence has strengthened local communities through
16 partnerships with schools, workforce development initiatives, and charitable contributions
17 that benefit residents across the region; and
18 WHEREAS, Cheniere Energy's commitment to safety, operational excellence, and
